## Step 1: Go to Terraform working directory
```bash
cd /home/bob/terraform
```
ğŸ“ Step 2: Create main.tf (ONLY this file)
vi main.tf


Paste the entire content below â¬‡ï¸

provider "aws" {
  region = "us-east-1"
}

resource "aws_security_group" "devops_sg" {
  name        = "devops-sg"
  description = "Security group for Nautilus App Servers"
  vpc_id      = data.aws_vpc.default.id

  ingress {
    description = "HTTP"
    from_port   = 80
    to_port     = 80
    protocol    = "tcp"
    cidr_blocks = ["0.0.0.0/0"]
  }

  ingress {
    description = "SSH"
    from_port   = 22
    to_port     = 22
    protocol    = "tcp"
    cidr_blocks = ["0.0.0.0/0"]
  }

  egress {
    from_port   = 0
    to_port     = 0
    protocol    = "-1"
    cidr_blocks = ["0.0.0.0/0"]
  }
}

data "aws_vpc" "default" {
  default = true
}


Save and exit:

:wq

ğŸš€ Step 3: Initialize Terraform
terraform init

ğŸ” Step 4: Validate configuration (optional but safe)
terraform validate


Expected:

Success! The configuration is valid.

â–¶ï¸ Step 5: Apply Terraform
terraform apply


When prompted:

Enter a value: yes

âœ… Step 6: Confirm success

You should see:

Apply complete! Resources: 1 added, 0 changed, 0 destroyed.

ğŸ§¾ Final Verification (Optional)
terraform show | grep devops-sg
